All courses of action are risky, so prudence is not in avoiding danger (it&rsquo;s impossible), but calculating risk and acting decisively. Make mistakes of ambition and not mistakes of sloth. Develop the strength to do bold things, not the strength to suffer. &ndash; Chapter III: Of Mixed Princedoms1
